Cortisol, dehydroepiandrosterone, and estradiol measured over 24 hours in women with childhood sexual abuse-related posttraumatic stress disorder. Preclinical studies have shown long-term alterations in several hormonal systems including cortisol, dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA) and DHEA-Sulfate, and estradiol. The purpose of this study was to assess cortisol, DHEA, and estradiol over a 24-hour period in women with early childhood sexual abuse and posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) with early abuse and without PTSD